===Etymology===
From earlier {{m|en|gamel}}, from {{inh|en|enm|*gamlen}}, {{m|enm|*gamelen}}, variant of {{der|en|enm|gamenen}}, from {{der|en|ang|gæmnian}}, {{m|ang|gamnian}}, {{m|ang|gamenian||to joke; play}}, related to Old English {{m|ang|gamen||joy; mirth; pleasure; entertainment; pastime; sport; game}}, equivalent to {{suffix|en|game|le}}. Compare Old Danish {{m|gmq-oda|gammel}}, Middle High German {{m|gmh|gamel||pleasure; fun}}. More at {{l|en|game}}.

